      "span_text": "Rural-urban differences in the prevalence and predictors of depression among adolescents in South Africa and not necessarily the presence or absence of psychiatric disorders.  25] The independent variables used in this study were: age (15 -19 years); gender (male/female); education (primary/ post primary); race (black African/non-black); individual income (<ZAR1 000/ZAR1 000 -R10 000/>ZAR10 000), and province of residence (any of the nine SA provinces)."
